    • Method Detail

      • parseErrors

        void parseErrors(java.io.File file,
                 ProgressDialog pd)
          throws java.io.IOException
        Parses through the file and generates the errors. It also makes calls to the ProgressDialog object to see how far through the file we are. Different errors will be made depending on how the user is searching, either through checkbox or through a refined logic search.
        Parameters:
        file - The logfile that the user wants to parse through
        pd - A create progress dialog object that keeps track of the parsing progress
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • parseArrowError

        java.lang.Object[] parseArrowError(java.io.BufferedReader logbr,
                                   java.lang.String timeStamp,
                                   java.lang.String[] currArray)
                            throws java.io.IOException
        Creates the entry for an arrow error, a special case since arrow errors can be made of multiple lines in a logfile
        Parameters:
        logbr - The buffered reader reading through the logfile
        timeStamp - The timestamp of the line where the first arrow was encountered
        currArray - An array containing the elements of the above line, split by " "
        Returns:
        Returns an entry that can be added to errorData
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • updateProgress

        void updateProgress(java.lang.String addLine)
        Updates the progress on the ProgressDialog by dividing progress (the lines read so far) by the total file size. The progress bar is only updated if the generated percent (integer of the division) is greater than oldPercent.

      • compareTimeStamp

        Returns:
        True if the time is within the bounds, false otherwise
